## Diagnosis

The nav logo "Yilan Gao" is wrapping because the flex container is distributing space without protecting the logo as a fixed, non-shrinkable unit. The logo text has no explicit `whitespace-nowrap` + `flex-shrink-0` guard, so when the viewport narrows, the flex algorithm treats it as fair game for compression. The identity blurb beside it is also likely in the same flex row without a clear shrink hierarchy established.

**Anti-pattern: AP-072** — *Unprotected identity-critical text in a shared flex context* — failing to declare `flex-shrink: 0` + `white-space: nowrap` on brand-identity elements, allowing the layout engine to collapse them.

---

## Root Cause

```
nav flex container
├── Logo "Yilan Gao"        ← no shrink protection, no nowrap
└── Identity blurb          ← allowed to shrink, but not explicitly declared
```

Both children share the same flex shrink budget. The logo has no explicit claim to "I never give up space." This is a missing **flex priority contract**.

---

## Fix

### 1. The Nav Component

Assuming your nav lives at something like `src/components/nav/Nav.tsx` (adjust to your actual path):

```tsx
// src/components/nav/Nav.tsx

export function Nav() {
  return (
    <nav className="nav">
      <div className="nav__identity">
        {/* LOGO: Core identity — NEVER wraps, NEVER shrinks. Principle: CAP-016 */}
        <span className="nav__logo">Yilan Gao</span>

        {/* BLURB: Secondary identity — MAY wrap under compression */}
        <span className="nav__blurb">
          Designer, AI systems experience...
        </span>
      </div>

      {/* rest of nav items */}
    </nav>
  )
}
```

### 2. The CSS

If you are using a global stylesheet or a CSS module (e.g., `src/components/nav/Nav.css` or within your Tailwind layer):

```css
/* src/styles/components/nav.css
 *
 * LAYOUT PRIORITY CONTRACT — Navigation
 * ─────────────────────────────────────
 * Rule CAP-016: Core identity elements (logo, brand name) must be
 * declared flex-shrink: 0 + white-space: nowrap at all times.
 * They do NOT participate in the flex compression budget.
 * Secondary elements (taglines, blurbs) absorb all compression instead.
 *
 * This is a permanent, non-negotiable principle for this project.
 * Do not remove these properties without a design principal decision.
 */

.nav {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: var(--space-4);
  padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-6);
}

.nav__identity {
  display: flex;
  align-items: baseline;
  gap: var(--space-3);
  /* Allow the identity block itself to shrink as a unit,
     but its LOGO child will never participate */
  min-width: 0;
}

.nav__logo {
  /* ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
   * ║  PROTECTED — Core identity. Never wraps. Never       ║
   * ║  shrinks. See CAP-016.                               ║
   * ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝ */
  flex-shrink: 0;          /* refuses to give up any space */
  white-space: nowrap;     /* cannot be broken across lines */
  font-family: var(--font-display);
  font-size: var(--text-lg);
  font-weight: var(--font-semibold);
  letter-spacing: var(--tracking-tight);
}

.nav__blurb {
  /* Secondary identity — absorbs ALL compression.
   * Allowed to wrap. min-width: 0 required to actually shrink. */
  flex-shrink: 1;
  min-width: 0;
  /* Optionally clamp to 2 lines max if you want tight control */
  /* overflow: hidden; */
  /* display: -webkit-box; */
  /* -webkit-line-clamp: 2; */
  /* -webkit-box-orient: vertical; */
  font-size: var(--text-sm);
  color: var(--color-muted);
}
```

### 3. If you are using Tailwind utility classes directly

```tsx
// src/components/nav/Nav.tsx

export function Nav() {
  return (
    <nav className="flex items-center gap-4 px-6 py-3">
      <div className="flex items-baseline gap-3 min-w-0">

        {/*
          * CAP-016: PROTECTED LOGO
          * flex-shrink-0 + whitespace-nowrap = non-negotiable identity lock
          * Never remove these two classes from this element.
          */}
        <span className="flex-shrink-0 whitespace-nowrap font-display text-lg font-semibold tracking-tight">
          Yilan Gao
        </span>

        {/*
          * Secondary identity — shrinks and wraps freely.
          * min-w-0 is required: without it, flex items ignore overflow.
          */}
        <span className="flex-shrink min-w-0 text-sm text-muted">
          Designer, AI systems experience...
        </span>

      </div>

      {/* nav links etc. */}
    </nav>
  )
}
```

---

## The Codified Principle (add this to your design system docs)

Create or append to `docs/principles/layout-priority.md`:

```markdown
# CAP-016 — Layout Priority Contract: Core Identity Protection

## Rule
Any element that constitutes **core brand identity** — wordmarks,
logo text, personal name in nav context — must be declared as:

  flex-shrink: 0
  white-space: nowrap

at all times, in all viewport conditions. These elements do NOT
participate in the flex compression budget under any circumstances.

## Hierarchy
1. **Protected (never compresses):** Logo, brand name, wordmark
2. **Compressible (wraps freely):** Taglines, blurbs, secondary descriptors
3. **Hidden (disappears before logo is touched):** Auxiliary nav items

## Why
A name that breaks across two lines reads as broken. Visual integrity
of the identity is more important than fitting any secondary content.
The layout should sacrifice everything else before it sacrifices the name.

## Implementation checklist
- [ ] `flex-shrink: 0` on the logo element
- [ ] `white-space: nowrap` on the logo element
- [ ] `min-width: 0` on any flex sibling that should absorb compression
- [ ] Comment in source citing CAP-016 so future developers know it is intentional
```

---

## Principle

**flex-shrink-0 + whitespace-nowrap is an identity declaration, not a style choice.** The logo is a proper noun. It has one correct rendering. The layout's job is to protect it and renegotiate everything else around it — not to ask the name to compromise its form. Secondary content absorbs pressure; identity does not.
